## 🎯 What This Project Is

A multi-agent AI system that autonomously researches any topic and produces a comprehensive, cited report. Instead of one LLM call, a team of specialized agents plans the research, searches multiple sources, reads and extracts facts, cross-references them, critiques the draft for quality, and only then writes the final report — looping back to re-research if the critique score is too low.

**Core differentiators vs. a basic single-agent RAG project:**

| Feature | Basic Version | This Project |
|---|---|---|
| Agents | 2–3 simple agents | 6 specialized agents with distinct roles |
| Orchestration | Sequential chain | Stateful graph (LangGraph) with conditional edges |
| Reflection | None | Critic agent with iterative refinement loop |
| Memory | Short-term only | Hybrid (short-term + long-term + episodic) |
| Observability | Print statements | Structured logs / Langfuse tracing + custom metrics |
| Evaluation | Manual | Automated RAGAS + custom metrics |
| Cost Control | Ignored | Per-agent token/call tracking to stay within free-tier limits |
| Human-in-Loop | None | Approval checkpoints at critical steps |
| UI | None / basic | Streamlit app with live agent progress |

**Note:** This project is built entirely with free-tier resources — no paid OpenAI or Claude API usage. LLM inference uses **Groq's free tier** as primary and **Google Gemini's free tier** as fallback, vector storage uses **Chroma Cloud** (hosted, free tier), and search uses free/no-key APIs.

