### 🤖 The 6 Agents

| Agent | Role | Key Responsibilities |
|---|---|---|
| 🧠 **Planner** | Strategy | Decomposes the query into 5–10 sub-questions, creates the research plan, decides depth |
| 🔍 **Searcher** | Discovery | Queries free search APIs (DuckDuckGo, Google Scholar via `scholarly`) and academic APIs, scrapes sites with Playwright |
| 📖 **Reader** | Comprehension | Chunks content, extracts key facts, stores in vector DB with metadata |
| 🧪 **Synthesizer** | Analysis | Cross-references sources, identifies contradictions, builds a knowledge graph |
| 🕵️ **Critic** | Quality Control | Fact-checks claims, scores relevance/accuracy, triggers re-research if quality is low |
| ✍️ **Writer** | Output | Generates the structured report with citations and an executive summary |

**Reflection loop:** the Critic scores the draft on factuality, completeness, and citation quality. If the score is below threshold (e.g. 0.8) and iteration count < 3, control routes back to the Searcher for another pass; otherwise it proceeds to the Writer.

