## 🧠 LLM Setup (no OpenAI / no Claude)

- **Primary:** [Groq](https://groq.com) API (`GROQ_API_KEY`) — free tier, extremely fast inference on open models (e.g. Llama 3.1, Llama 3.3, Mixtral).
- **Fallback:** [Google Gemini](https://ai.google.dev) API (`GEMINI_API_KEY`) — free tier, used automatically if Groq errors out or is rate-limited.
- Agents talk to the LLM through a single thin wrapper (`llm/client.py`) that tries Groq first and falls back to Gemini on failure/rate-limit, so agent code never needs to know which provider served the call.
- Use a smaller/faster Groq model for high-frequency agents like Searcher/Reader, and a stronger model for Synthesizer/Critic/Writer where reasoning quality matters more.
- Both are free-tier hosted APIs (not local), so build in simple retry/backoff and respect each provider's rate limits.

